name: Acting Secretary Leigh M. Chapman
tweet: 57 years ago today, a group of Black citizens marched across the Edmund Pettus Bridge in Selma, AL, for civil rights. They were met with violence even though they chose non-violence. Their struggle led the way for the Voting Rights Act of 1965.  https://t.co/vKH6nqBVFk

name: Acting Secretary Leigh M. Chapman
tweet: Special Elections Notice ⚠️ If you live in the 19th, 24th, or 116th Legislative Districts, be sure to register to vote by March 21, 2022, so you can vote in the special election on April 5, 2022.

name: Acting Secretary Leigh M. Chapman
tweet: This month is #WomensHistoryMonth! I would like to honor those women who fought for the right to vote and those who are still fighting for justice and equality for every citizen.

name: Acting Secretary Leigh M. Chapman
tweet: I am honored to be entrusted to lead the incredible @PAStateDept team. We will work to continue to have free and fair elections, among many other responsibilities. I will strive to ensure that voting rights are protected, and to improve access to the ballot box for all PA voters.  https://t.co/oMhMN0K2hJ
